le=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104sij1665702974748.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sij1665702974748.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sij1665702974748.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"sij1665702974748\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Data Access with TXT\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The TXT connector reads and writes files that are defined in entity-to-connector assignments in the application assignment file.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1015002e56\">\n                        \n Reading and Writing Files\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sij1665702974748__p_d61475e1_d61476e1_d61477e1\">By default, when you open an entity, the TXT connector creates a new file or overwrites an existing file. You can override this default functionality, so that Uniface appends records to an existing file. Add the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/append</span> switch to each filename in an entity-to-connector assignment in the assignment file. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">my_entity.my_cs = $txt:my_file.ffd/append/uni=UTF16</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sij1665702974748__p_d61478e1_d61479e1_d61480e1\">On Windows and Unix, stream files are created, which means that the record terminator is written to the file in the Unicode encoding of the file.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sij1665702974748__p_d61481e1_d61482e1_d61483e1\">For all Unicode files, the BOM, Byte Order Mark, is written as the first bytes of data, followed by the data of the first record.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1015002e77\">\n                        \n I/O channels\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sij1665702974748__p_d61487e1_d61488e1_d61489e1\">One I/O channel is opened per file. The maximum number of I/O channels is dependent on the operating system.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1015002e86\">\n                        \n ProcScript Statements\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sij1665702974748__p_d61493e1_d61494e1_d61495e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">open</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">close</span> ProcScript statements are supported.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sij1665702974748__p_d61496e1_d61497e1_d61498e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">selectdb</span> statement and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">where</span> clause are not supported. If either of these statements is used, the TXT connector ignores it.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1015002e110\">\n                        \n Paths\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sij1665702974748__p_d61502e1_d61503e1_d61504e1\">Entity-to-connector paths should only be specified for files. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rgt1665702779523.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rgt1665702779523.html\" title=\"To configure the TXT connector and data access, edit the application assignment file.\">Configuring the TXT Connector</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sij1665702974748__p_d61505e1_d61506e1_d61507e1\">Logon information is not required.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sij1665702974748__p_d61508e1_d61509e1_d61510e1\">Wildcards are not supported.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531998\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531998\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Data Access with TXT Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Data Access with TXT The TXT connector reads and writes files that are defined in entity-to-connector assignments in the application assignment file. Reading and Writing Files By default, when you open an entity, the TXT connector creates a new file or overwrites an existing file. You can override this default functionality, so that Uniface appends records to an existing file. Add the /append switch to each filename in an entity-to-connector assignment in the assignment file. For example: my_entity.my_cs = $txt:my_file.ffd/append/uni=UTF16 Copy On Windows and Unix, stream files are created, which means that the record terminator is written to the file in the Unicode encoding of the file. For all Unicode files, the BOM, Byte Order Mark, is written as the first bytes of data, followed by the data of the first record. I/O channels One I/O channel is opened per file. The maximum number of I/O channels is dependent on the operating system. ProcScript Statements The open and close ProcScript statements are supported. The selectdb statement and where clause are not supported. If either of these statements is used, the TXT connector ignores it. Paths Entity-to-connector paths should only be specified for files. For more information, see Configuring the TXT Connector . Logon information is not required. Wildcards are not supported. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}